# Git Workflow

**Do not commit or push to Git unless the user explicitly requests it.**

- Wait for the user to ask for "commit", "push", "submit to Git", or similar.
- Do not decide on your own when to commit or push, even after completing tasks.
- When the user requests a commit: stage the relevant changes, create a clear commit message, commit, and push if requested.
